Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?
“Women versus Men in Literatures and Publications”

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")
A program that serves as a text analysis tool, allowing users to compare the linguistic portrayal of men and women in texts and articles. Users can input various pieces of text, and the program performs a comprehensive analysis to compare the diction used for each gender.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?

Our software will take an input of text from the user
It will divide the text into sentences referring to women and sentences referring to men using key words. (ex. Does the sentence contain “she”, “her”, “Ms.”, etc)
Then it will use the LIWC (linguistic inquiry and word count) dataset to detect the occurrences of certain diction in the text. For example, we will look at the difference in occurrence of body related words to shed light to objectification.
We will then output a multi column bar graph with different metrics on the x-axis such as Body, family, achieve, positive emotion, negative emotion, and the graph will show the difference in representation of men and women in certain contexts

